                    <span>Jim Wallis delivers and excellent work I was alerted to a few years ago.  This book forces Christians, from both sides of the political spectrum to examine what they believe, and why they believe it.  Especially pointed are the criticisms of how both sides have plans to deal with the poor, but both are off base in the extremes of what they are trying to accomplish.  Jim Wallis lives to serve the less-fortunate, and it shows in his servant attitude as he wrote this book.  I give Jim Wallis high marks for this book that challenges the status-quo.</span>
                  
