                    <span>i am not a christian, nor do i relate to the christian lifestyle yet i had no difficulty in recognizing the relevance and meaning in wallis's writing. the spirituality and morals he speaks of to salvage our collapsing society  should be found in all humans, regardless of religious affiliation. he does  a good job of including all walks of people. his focus on strictly black  and white racism, however, seemed narrow-minded to me because it neglected  the various other races and conflicts. he did get his point across, though.</span>
                  
              
